7,"south":34.8,"east":26.4,"west":23.5},"placeCount":14,"restaurantCount":14,"bestTimeToVisit":"Visit from April to May or September to October for enjoyable beach weather and exploration of Minoan ruins.","heroImage":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1579752284549-71eb9dd09f4b?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxDaGFuaWElMjBWZW5ldGlhbiUyMGhhcmJvciUyMHN1bnNldHxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzg0MDIwNDcxfDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Clay Banks"},"cardImage":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1579752284549-71eb9dd09f4b?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxDaGFuaWElMjBWZW5ldGlhbiUyMGhhcmJvciUyMHN1bnNldHxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzg0MDIwNDcxfDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080"}],"top10":[{"rank":1,"name":"Acropolis, Athens","placeId":"acropolis_athens","regionId":"attica","regionName":"Attica","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1603565816030-6b389eeb23cb?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxBY3JvcG9saXMlMkMlMjBBdGhlbnMlMjBHcmVlY2V8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4NDAxNzAzOHww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Constantinos Kollias"},"description":"The ancient hilltop citadel crowned by the Parthenon, dating to the 5th century BCE, stands as one of the world's most iconic symbols of Classical Greek civilization. Millions visit annually to witness the architectural masterpiece and explore the museums housing ancient Greek artifacts."},{"rank":2,"name":"Athens","placeId":"athens","regionId":"central_greece","regionName":"Central Greece","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1603565816030-6b389eeb23cb?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxBdGhlbnMlMjBBY3JvcG9saXMlMjBQYXJ0aGVub258ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzIwMjUyMnww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Constantinos Kollias"},"description":"Greece's vibrant capital and largest city, home to the iconic Acropolis, Parthenon, and countless ancient monuments alongside modern museums and bustling neighborhoods. The birthplace of Western democracy offers world-class antiquities, excellent food, and the energy of a contemporary Mediterranean metropolis."},{"rank":3,"name":"Santorini","placeId":"santorini","regionId":"southern_aegean","regionName":"Southern Aegean","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1580502304784-8985b7eb7260?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxTYW50b3JpbmklMjBHcmVlY2V8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4NDAyMDQyN3ww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"James Ting"},"description":"This volcanic Cycladic island is famous for its white-washed buildings with blue domes perched on dramatic cliffs overlooking the caldera and Aegean Sea. Visitors flock here for the spectacular sunsets, pristine beaches, and romantic atmosphere that have made it one of Europe's most photographed destinations."},{"rank":4,"name":"Mykonos","placeId":"mykonos","regionId":"southern_aegean","regionName":"Southern Aegean","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1601581875309-fafbf2d3ed3a?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxNeWtvbm9zJTIwR3JlZWNlfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODQwMjA0Mjl8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Johnny Africa"},"description":"This glamorous Cycladic island is renowned for its vibrant nightlife, cosmopolitan atmosphere, and beautiful beaches lined with upscale clubs and beach bars. Tourists visit for the energetic party scene, trendy restaurants, and the picturesque Cycladic charm of its chora town."},{"rank":5,"name":"Delphi","placeId":"delphi","regionId":"central_greece","regionName":"Central Greece","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1575233410558-2347d292e691?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxEZWxwaGklMjBUZW1wbGUlMjBvZiUyMEFwb2xsb3xlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzMjAyNTIwfDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"DiChatz"},"description":"Ancient sanctuary of Apollo and one of Greece's most sacred sites, perched dramatically on Mount Parnassus overlooking the valley below. The archaeological site features the iconic Temple of Apollo, the ancient theatre, and the museum housing the famous Charioteer statue, making it essential for understanding Classical Greek civilization."},{"rank":6,"name":"Crete","placeId":"crete","regionId":"crete","regionName":"Crete","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1616763866684-b215941fae5e?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxDcmV0ZSUyMEdyZWVjZXxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzg0MDIwNDk5fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Elena Dimaki"},"description":"Greece's largest island offers a unique blend of Minoan archaeological sites, stunning beaches, traditional villages, and diverse landscapes from beaches to mountains. Tourists are drawn to its rich history, excellent food, warm hospitality, and variety of activities including water sports and cultural exploration."},{"rank":7,"name":"Thessaloniki","placeId":"thessaloniki","regionId":"thessaloniki","regionName":"Central Macedonia","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1763567966641-2fd8676612b5?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxUaGVzc2Fsb25pa2klMjBXaGl0ZSUyMFRvd2VyJTIwd2F0ZXJmcm9udHxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzMjM4NjA4fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Mirkos Tsarouchidis"},"description":"Greece's second-largest city and capital of Central Macedonia, famous for its Byzantine churches, Ottoman architecture, and vibrant cultural scene. Essential for its museums, waterfront promenade, and as a gateway to the region's attractions."},{"rank":8,"name":"Rhodes","placeId":"rhodes","regionId":"southern_aegean","regionName":"Southern Aegean","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1587974136998-4fcc253b6183?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxSaG9kZXMlMjBHcmVlY2V8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4NDAyMDQzMXww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"CALIN STAN"},"description":"This southeastern Dodecanese island is famous for its pristine beaches, medieval Old Town with the Palace of Grand Masters, and pleasant climate year-round. Tourists flock here for water sports, historical exploration, nightlife, and easy access to nearby islands and Turkey."},{"rank":9,"name":"Meteora","placeId":"meteora","regionId":"central_greece","regionName":"Central Greece","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1687957324345-918d2f824f06?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxNZXRlb3JhJTIwbW9uYXN0ZXJpZXMlMjByb2Nrc3xlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzMjAyNTIzfDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"STEFANOS KERAMARIS"},"description":"Otherworldly landscape of towering rock pillars topped with ancient monasteries, creating one of the most visually stunning spiritual sites in Europe. Visitors can explore the monasteries perched atop these natural formations and hike among the dramatic geology that has captivated pilgrims and travelers for centuries."},{"rank":10,"name":"Olympia","placeId":"olympia","regionId":"peloponnese","regionName":"Peloponnese","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507475380673-1246fa72eeea?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxPbHltcGlhJTIwR3JlZWNlfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODQwMjAxMTZ8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Arthur Yeti"},"description":"The birthplace of the Olympic Games, this archaeological site in the Peloponnese contains the ruins of temples, stadiums, and training grounds dating back millennia. History enthusiasts and sports